MAXADMIN(1)
===========
:doctype: manpage
:man version:  @VERSION@

NAME
----

maxadmin - the MaxScale administrative and monitor client


SYNOPSIS
--------

*maxadmin* ['OPTIONS'] ['command file' | 'command']


DESCRIPTION
-----------

...

OPTIONS
-------

*-u, --user=*'username'::     
  The user name to use for the connection 
  (default: *admin*)

*-p, --password=*'password'::	
  The user password, if not given the password will be prompted for interactively
  (default: *skysql*)
  
*-h, --hostname=*'host/ip'::
  The maxscale host to connecto to
  (default: *localhost*)

*-P, --port=*'number'::       	
  The port to use for the connection
  (default: *6603*)

*-v, --version*::
   print version information and exit

*-?, --help*::	
  print help text and exit

Any remaining arguments are treated as MaxScale commands or a file
containing commands to execute.

EXIT STATUS
-----------

0 if connection to a *maxscale(1)* daemon was successful, 1 otherwise.


